page_id: S4-LNX-03
title: Repository folder on Linux
description: Explain local folder risk before the Linux repository continues to open, init, or adopt confirmation.
summary:
  - Folder: /home/you/AreaMatrix
  - Type: Local folder
  - Type: External drive
  - Type: Network mount
  - Type: Sync folder
  - Type: Unknown
  - Writable: Yes/No
states:
  checking: Checking folder...
  empty_path: Choose a repository folder first.
  local: This is the recommended setup for Linux.
  network: Network drives may delay or reorder file events. Run a rescan if changes look out of date.
  sync: AreaMatrix does not manage your sync provider. Conflict files will be shown for review when detected.
  unknown: Unknown
  readonly: The folder is not writable. Choose another folder before initializing or importing.
confirmation:
  checkbox: I understand this location may not report changes reliably.
actions:
  - Continue
  - Choose Another Folder
  - Open Folder
safety:
  - The page calls validate_repo_path through LinuxRepositoryCoreBridge.
  - The page routes to S4-X-04 or S4-X-05 for init/adopt confirmation before init_repo can run.
  - The page does not create, delete, move, rename, overwrite, sudo, or chmod user files.
  - C4-17 platform capabilities are out of scope for this C4-10 page-feature task.
